 Carnoy's solution is a tissue fixative who has alcohol allowing for fat clearing along with tissue fixation.

 Previous studies demonstrated this ability and the investigators introduced this for patients with rectal cancer who has undergone preoperative chemoradiaton.

 This subgroup of patients have a very low lymph node yield.

